25 in accordance with the customer's service agreement.
26 Sec. 16. As used in this chapter, "system average interruption
27 duration index", or "SAIDI", means an index that:
28 (1) indicates the total duration of sustained service
29 interruptions for an electricity supplier's average customer
30 during a specified period; and
31 (2) is calculated by determining the quotient of:
32 (A) the sum of sustained service interruption durations in
33 minutes for the specified period; divided by
34 (B) the total number of customers;
35 in accordance with IEEE 1336.
36 Sec. 17. As used in this chapter, "system average interruption
