14 Sec. 23. (a) For each rate year in an electricity supplier's
15 multi-year rate plan, the commission shall determine a customer
16 affordability performance metric for that electricity supplier by
17 calculating the difference between:
18 (1) the average annual percentage change (rounded to nearest
19 one-tenth percent (0.1%)) in the electricity supplier's average
20 monthly residential bill over the course of the most recently
21 concluded five (5) calendar years (normalized for weather if
22 not otherwise normalized for weather through a rate
23 adjustment mechanism described in section 1(b)(3) of this
24 chapter); minus
25 (2) the average annual percentage change (rounded to nearest
26 one-tenth percent (0.1%)) in seasonally adjusted electricity
27 prices for the United States as measured by the Consumer
28 Price Index, as published by the United States Bureau of
29 Labor Statistics, over the course of the most recently
30 concluded five (5) calendar years;
31 as reported in the most recent customer affordability performance
32 report submitted to the commission by the electricity supplier
33 under section 18 of this chapter. The difference calculated under
34 this subsection is the electricity supplier's customer affordability
35 performance metric for the rate year.
36 (b) If the electricity supplier's customer affordability
37 performance metric under subsection (a) is a positive number that
38 exceeds two (2) percentage points, the commission shall adjust the
39 electricity supplier's authorized return for the rate year downward
40 by not more than one (1) basis point.
41 (c) If the electricity supplier's customer affordability
42 performance metric under subsection (a) is a negative number that
2026 IN 1002—LS 7032/DI 101

20
1 when multiplied by negative one (-1) exceeds two (2) percentage
2 points, the commission shall adjust the electricity supplier's
3 authorized return for the rate year upward by not more than one
4 (1) basis point.
5 Sec. 24. (a) For each rate year included in an electricity
6 supplier's multi-year rate plan, the commission shall determine,
7 using the most recent service restoration performance report
8 submitted to the commission by the electricity supplier under
9 section 19 of this chapter, a normalized service restoration
10 performance metric for that electricity supplier in the following
11 manner:
12 STEP ONE: Calculate the sum of the electricity supplier's
13 average:
14 (A) SAIDI;
15 (B) SAIFI; and
16 (C) CAIDI;
17 over the course of the five (5) calendar years immediately
18 preceding the most recently concluded calendar year,
19 excluding major event days, for the electricity supplier's
20 system in Indiana as a whole.
21 STEP TWO: Calculate the sum of the electricity supplier's:
22 (A) SAIDI;
23 (B) SAIFI; and
24 (C) CAIDI;
25 for the most recently concluded calendar year, excluding
26 major event days, for the electricity supplier's system in
27 Indiana as a whole.
28 STEP THREE: Calculate the difference between the STEP
29 ONE result minus the STEP TWO result.
30 STEP FOUR: Calculate the quotient of the STEP THREE
31 result divided by the STEP ONE result, rounded to the
32 nearest one-hundredth (0.01).
33 STEP FIVE: Calculate the product of one hundred (100)
34 multiplied by the STEP FOUR result. This product is the
35 electricity supplier's normalized service restoration
36 performance metric for the rate year.
37 (b) If the electricity supplier's normalized service restoration
38 performance metric under subsection (a) is a positive number that
39 exceeds five (5), the commission shall adjust the electricity
40 supplier's authorized return for the rate year upward by not more
41 than one-half (0.50) basis point.
42 (c) If the electricity supplier's normalized service restoration
2026 IN 1002—LS 7032/DI 101

21
1 performance metric under subsection (a) is a negative number that
2 when multiplied by negative one (-1) exceeds five (5), the
3 commission shall adjust the electricity supplier's authorized return
4 for the rate year downward by not more than one-half (0.50) basis
5 point.
6 (d) For each rate year included in an electricity supplier's
7 multi-year rate plan, the commission shall determine, using the
8 most recent service restoration performance report submitted to
9 the commission by the electricity supplier under section 19 of this
10 chapter, a MED service restoration performance metric for that
11 electricity supplier in the following manner:
12 STEP ONE: Calculate the sum of the electricity supplier's
13 average:
14 (A) SAIDI;
15 (B) SAIFI; and
16 (C) CAIDI;
17 over the course of the five (5) calendar years immediately
18 preceding the most recently concluded calendar year,
19 including major event days only, for the electricity supplier's
20 system in Indiana as a whole.
21 STEP TWO: Calculate the sum of the electricity supplier's:
22 (A) SAIDI;
23 (B) SAIFI; and
24 (C) CAIDI;
25 for the most recently concluded calendar year, including
26 major event days only, for the electricity supplier's system in
27 Indiana as a whole.
28 STEP THREE: Calculate the difference between the STEP
29 ONE result minus the STEP TWO result.
30 STEP FOUR: Calculate the quotient of the STEP THREE
31 result divided by the STEP ONE result, rounded to the
32 nearest one-hundredth (0.01).
33 STEP FIVE: Calculate the product of one hundred (100)
34 multiplied by the STEP FOUR result. This product is the
35 electricity supplier's MED service restoration performance
36 metric for the rate year.
37 (e) If the electricity supplier's MED service restoration
38 performance metric under subsection (d) is a positive number that
39 exceeds five (5), the commission shall adjust the electricity
